OL,3,CIt's a 'no-brainer': Prison officers
OL,4,Ccall for stab vests in dangerous jails
OL,6,FFollowing the meeting with the justice
OL,7,Fsecretary on Wednesday 23 April,
OL,8,FPrison Officers' Association chair
OL,9,FMark Fairhurst described the proposed
OL,10,Fchanges as "an absolute no-brainer."
OL,12,FHe said: "We welcome the rapid review
OL,13,Fwhich I know is going to be completed
OL,14,Fwithin weeks, not months, with
OL,15,Frecommendations."
OL,17,FMr Fairhurst added: "You need stab
OL,18,Fvests in our prisons, specifically in
OL,19,Fhigh-security estates and high-risk
OL,20,Fareas like segregation units and close-
OL,21,Fsupervision centres.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/5
